A group, Bomadi and Patani Political Mandate has called on the Member Representing Bomadi/Patani Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives, Hon. Nicholas Ebomo Mutu to re-contest for the federal constituency seat come 2023. The group made the call at a press briefing in Asaba, the Delta State capital, shortly after endorsing him as their preferred House of Representatives candidate for the 2023 general election. According to the group, Hon. Mutu stands taller than all the aspirants who have shown interest in terms of achievements and development strides because as a member representing the constituency in time past, he is more experienced and positioned to deliver more democratic dividends desired by Bomadi and Patani Local Government Areas constituents. The Publicity Secretary of BPPM, Comrade Enebibulouami Amabri who spoke with newsmen revealed that the choice of Rt. Hon. Nicholas Ebomo Mutu is easy, given his wealth of experience and political antecedents. The group said, “It was easy for us to endorse the candidacy of Rt. Hon. Mutu. This is a man with a wealth of experience in politics, tested and trusted with the peoples’ resources and has delivered in countless occasions.” “If you look at all the people who have indicated an interest in the 2023 House of Representatives, Bomadi/Patani Federal Constituency, Rt. Hon. Mutu stands tall amongst them, in terms of integrity, leadership traits, age, and experience.” The group called on all constituents who are yet to decide their choice of candidate for the 2023 election, to pitch their tent with Mutu, saying he is the best choice for Bomadi/Patani Federal Constituency.